{"TopicId":182763,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.4.5/1.6.1]Remote Joystick","CreatedByName":"AST_SIL_834","CreatedById":156333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T03:22:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"AST_SIL_834","CreatedById":156333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T03:22:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod allows you to use your Android device to remotely control a vessel\u00A0in KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDownload\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n(including both the mod and the android app)\u003Cbr\u003E\n- \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/xdedss/KSP_RemoteJoystick/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EGithub\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n- \u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/2105/Remote%20Joystick\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESpaceDock\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EInstall\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Drag the RemoteJoystick folder into your GameData Folder\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Install the .apk file on your android device\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EUse\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Make sure your PC and android device are connected with the same local area network.\u003Cbr\u003E\n- When you fly a vessel, the mod icon will appear. Right click it to start the server. The icon will then turn yellow.\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Run the android app, enter the local ip of your PC, click the Connect button. The ingame icon will turn green if the connection is successful.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Dkvwoxx.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u002241\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Dkvwoxx.png\u0022 width=\u002251\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Enjoy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EExplanations about settings\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EInput curve factor: \u003C/strong\u003EIf set to 0, the output to vessel\u0027s control will be exactly same as input. If\u00A0set to 1, the output will be the same as input only when input is small. As input increases, the output increases slower.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EInput smooth factor:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0 If set to 0, the output will response immediately when input changes. If set to 1, the output will be smooth and delayed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nNote that you should always use the corresponding android app version with the mod. If you are going to update the mod, you should also update the android app.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EScreenshot\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224o9BzDh.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022491\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/4o9BzDh.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESource\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/xdedss/KSP_RemoteJoystick\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMod\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/xdedss/KSP_AndroidJoystick\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAndroid app\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003EAll contents are\u00A0under the MIT License\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#2980b9;font-size:14px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ENetwork Usage\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis mod contacts with the\u00A0Android app\u00A0using socket.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe data from Android device to PC only includs joystick positions, steering, throttle and action groups, encoded to a 8Byte data, sent 20times/sec.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe data from PC to Android device only includs vessel\u0027s velocity, rotation, longitude and latitude, encoded to a 28Byte data, sent 20 times/sec.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChangelog\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003Ev0.4 for KSP 1.6.1\u003Cbr\u003E\n2019-03-17\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nImproved layout\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSettings panel\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdjustable input smooth and curve\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdjustable unit(m, feet, m/s, km/h, mph)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSwitch between navball and nav-screen\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAbort, map and timewarp buttons.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003ETodo\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u221A\u00A0UI scale for different resolutions\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u221A\u00A0Add longitude and latitude and altitude display\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u221A\u00A0Add velocity indicator on navball\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Add\u00A0target indicator on navball\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Switch \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E mode\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Switch to docking mode\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u221A\u00A0Timewarp\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u221A Map view toggle\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsuggestions are welcomed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-17T15:17:50Z\u0022 title=\u002203/17/2019 03:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by AST_SIL_834\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T03:43:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forums AST!\u00A0\u00A0 This is a really cool idea!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote though, we\u0027ll need you to select a license for the mod.\u00A0 So please choose one, and edit your post.\u00A0\u00A0 Thanks.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFew suggestions:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) With the upcoming altitude indicator revamp, maybe adding that in the dead space to the top left would be cool.\u00A0\u00A0 This would help with flying planes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) Adding the various indicators on the navball, like prograde, etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3) Being able to swap modes, into a docking mode, but not like the goofy stock one that exists.\u00A0\u00A0 So you hit a button, and instead of emulating WASD, it would emulate IJKL.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4) Being able to select the various \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E modes from within the App.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AST_SIL_834","CreatedById":156333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T03:53:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223555393\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552189406\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forums AST!\u00A0\u00A0 This is a really cool idea!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote though, we\u0027ll need you to select a license for the mod.\u00A0 So please choose one, and edit your post.\u00A0\u00A0 Thanks.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFew suggestions:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) With the upcoming altitude indicator revamp, maybe adding that in the dead space to the top left would be cool.\u00A0\u00A0 This would help with flying planes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) Adding the various indicators on the navball, like prograde, etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3) Being able to swap modes, into a docking mode, but not like the goofy \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Estock one that exists.\u00A0\u00A0 So you hit a button, and instead of emulating WASD, it would emulate IJKL.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4) Being able to select the various \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E modes from within the App.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for your reply!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m gonna add these to my todo list\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T13:26:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/69272-steve_v/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002269272\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/69272-steve_v/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@steve_v\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Joysticks finally back on Linux!...kind of...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Barzon","CreatedById":185383,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T14:20:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do I install the phone app?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AST_SIL_834","CreatedById":156333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T14:53:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223555626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552227608\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185383\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Barzon Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, Barzon Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do I install the phone app?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe file \u0022KSP_AndroidJoystick_v0.3.apk\u0022\u00A0is inside the zip file. If you have an Android phone, then\u00A0you can send the .apk\u00A0file to the phone and install it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MMG","CreatedById":149289,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-11T20:11:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally a replacemnet for actual joystick or screen joystick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood work there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-13T12:57:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I installed the app but its not showing up with all my other apps and i can only run it when I install it once.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-13T19:52:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGot it working! This is a great mod, I will try to go to orbit and back using just my phone!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-13T22:15:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223555386\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552188131\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AST_SIL_834\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E3\u200E/\u200E9\u200E/\u200E2019 at 10:22 PM, AST_SIL_834 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod allows you to use your Android device to remotely control a vessel\u00A0in KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I went to kerbin orbit and back using just my phone! I like the mod but a better looking UI and more things added like time warping and a button to toggle map view on/off would be nice if you could add them. \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/156333-ast_sil_834/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022156333\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/156333-ast_sil_834/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@AST_SIL_834\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/SI-KRt2neGI?start=111\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m thinking it would look like this (maybe make some buttons slightly smaller for more room?):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022zkkpNVz.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022575\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/zkkpNVz.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-13T22:24:10Z\u0022 title=\u002203/13/2019 10:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 13, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Johnster_Space_Program\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AST_SIL_834","CreatedById":156333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-13T23:11:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223558637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552515341\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187334\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Johnster_Space_Program\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n51 minutes ago, Johnster_Space_Program said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I went to kerbin orbit and back using just my phone! I like the mod but a better looking UI and more things added like time warping and a button to toggle map view on/off would be nice if you could add them. \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/156333-ast_sil_834/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022156333\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/156333-ast_sil_834/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@AST_SIL_834\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/SI-KRt2neGI?start=111\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m thinking it would look like this (maybe make some buttons slightly smaller for more room?):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/zkkpNVz.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022zkkpNVz.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022575\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/zkkpNVz.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat job! I\u0027m working on UI improvement to adapt to different screen resolution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-13T23:51:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223558698\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552518710\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AST_SIL_834\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, AST_SIL_834 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat job! I\u0027m working on UI improvement to adapt to different screen resolution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! Will you also add at least some of the features I think you should like map view toggle and maybe timewarp? Also, great work so far!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-14T00:14:16Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2019 12:14  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Johnster_Space_Program\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AST_SIL_834","CreatedById":156333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-14T00:41:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223558735\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552521115\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187334\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Johnster_Space_Program\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, Johnster_Space_Program said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! Will you also add at least some of the features I think you should like map view toggle and maybe timewarp? Also, great work so far!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure, I\u0027m adding them to my todo list. Thanks for suggestions!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-14T12:18:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223558791\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552524067\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AST_SIL_834\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, AST_SIL_834 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure, I\u0027m adding them to my todo list. Thanks for suggestions!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, when is the next update coming out? I\u0027m excited to see what it adds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AST_SIL_834","CreatedById":156333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-14T13:57:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223559202\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552565908\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187334\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Johnster_Space_Program\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Johnster_Space_Program said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, when is the next update coming out? I\u0027m excited to see what it adds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere will be improvements\u00A0on art style and several new features(according to suggestions).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a\u00A0lot of work to do and it\u0027s hard to say how long it will take to finish. Maybe next Monday.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AST_SIL_834","CreatedById":156333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-17T15:17:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:24px;\u0022\u003Ev0.4 for KSP 1.6.1\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EChanges\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#24292e;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nImproved layout\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSettings panel\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdjustable input smooth and curve\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdjustable unit(m, feet, m/s, km/h, mph)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSwitch between navball and nav-screen\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAbort, map and timewarp buttons.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EExplanations about settings\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EInput curve factor\u003C/strong\u003E:\u00A0If set to 0, the output to vessel\u0027s control will be exactly same as input. If\u00A0set to 1, the output will be the same as input only when input is small. As input increases, the output increases slower.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EInput smooth factor\u003C/strong\u003E:\u00A0 If set to 0, the output will response immediately when input changes. If set to 1, the output will be smooth and delayed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022csf6Dft.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022491\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/csf6Dft.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sIxYt2W.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022491\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/sIxYt2W.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Barzon","CreatedById":185383,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-17T15:35:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you put the mobile app on the play store or something, because for the love of god, I cannot make it work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FirenzeEzio","CreatedById":191740,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-18T11:33:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like this very much. he\u0027s practical, and he\u0027s great.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AST_SIL_834","CreatedById":156333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-18T12:24:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223561620\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552836900\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185383\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Barzon Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, Barzon Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you put the mobile app on the play store or something, because for the love of god, I cannot make it work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you tell me exactly what problem you got? I need more information to give you support.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-18T12:25:38Z\u0022 title=\u002203/18/2019 12:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 18, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by AST_SIL_834\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-18T22:22:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223561604\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552835830\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AST_SIL_834\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E3\u200E/\u200E17\u200E/\u200E2019 at 11:17 AM, AST_SIL_834 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:24px;\u0022\u003Ev0.4 for KSP 1.6.1\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EChanges\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#24292e;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nImproved layout\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSettings panel\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdjustable input smooth and curve\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdjustable unit(m, feet, m/s, km/h, mph)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSwitch between navball and nav-screen\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAbort, map and timewarp buttons.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EExplanations about settings\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EInput curve factor\u003C/strong\u003E:\u00A0If set to 0, the output to vessel\u0027s control will be exactly same as input. If\u00A0set to 1, the output will be the same as input only when input is small. As input increases, the output increases slower.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EInput smooth factor\u003C/strong\u003E:\u00A0 If set to 0, the output will response immediately when input changes. If set to 1, the output will be smooth and delayed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/csf6Dft.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022csf6Dft.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022491\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/csf6Dft.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/sIxYt2W.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sIxYt2W.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022491\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/sIxYt2W.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for making a new update with the changes I wanted! Now I can go to the mun and back with my phone (or at least try)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Barzon","CreatedById":185383,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-22T22:33:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223562144\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552911898\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AST_SIL_834\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/18/2019 at 12:24 PM, AST_SIL_834 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you tell me exactly what problem you got? I need more information to give you support.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just dont\u00A0know where to put it. I tryed in some places (I cant remember where), and it didnt\u00A0work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-22T23:01:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou got specs for your network packet data\u00A0structures\u00A0so people can design their own client side (for example raspi or esp8266/esp32) as an alternate to the droid app (i got an old android tablet but its so old i doubt it would work).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-22T23:02:51Z\u0022 title=\u002203/22/2019 11:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 22, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Nuke\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-24T10:31:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223555595\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552224360\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105132\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klgraham1013\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/11/2019 at 2:26 AM, klgraham1013 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJoysticks finally back on Linux!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCommunity member develops cross-platform remote input layer, releases it for free and provides support.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nProfessional game development company fails utterly to support even local input devices, blames third-party engine and calls it a day.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis mod is indeed awesome. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt\u0027s just a shame we \u003Cem\u003Eneed\u003C/em\u003E mods to work around Squad\u0027s ineptitude and/or apathy. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-24T11:21:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223567314\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221553423502\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EIt\u0027s just a shame we \u003Cem\u003Eneed\u003C/em\u003E mods to work around Squad\u0027s ineptitude and/or apathy. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDude.\u00A0 We\u0027ve been doing it for years.\u00A0 Mods make KSP worth playing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-25T09:54:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223567324\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221553426485\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105132\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klgraham1013\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 hours ago, klgraham1013 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMods make KSP worth playing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes they do, I\u0027d have given up on the game long ago without them. The only reason I update the game at all now is new mod releases.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nMods adding missing functionality is awesome, it\u0027s been awesome since day-one.\u003Cbr\u003E\nMods fixing \u003Cem\u003Enew\u003C/em\u003E idiotic regressions in the stock game 6\u002B years of development in is ridiculous. Regressions are Squads job.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s been shown repeatedly that fixing input support is quite possible, and there are now 3 mods that I am aware of which do so.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe excuse that it is too difficult is long dead. The excuse that it would take longer than waiting for unity to fix it is long dead. All that remains is Squad being either too lazy or too incompetent - and I find the latter pretty unconvincing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-25T10:00:50Z\u0022 title=\u002203/25/2019 10:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 25, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by steve_v\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}